description: Deregisters the specified AMI. A deregistered AMI can't be used to launch new instances. If a deregistered EBS-backed AMI matches a Recycle Bin retention rule, it moves to the Recycle Bin for the specified retention period. It can be restored before its retention period expires, after which it is permanently deleted. If the deregistered AMI doesn't match a retention rule, it is permanently deleted immediately. For more information, see Recycle Bin in the Amazon EBS User Guide.
